## Component patterns

### Server components by default
Use server components for all data-fetching. Drop to `'use client'` only for:
- Interactive search/filter UI
- Forms
- Real-time updates
- Anything requiring browser APIs

### Data fetching pattern
```typescript
// app/(app)/directory/page.tsx — server component
import { searchMembers } from '@/lib/search'
import { MemberGrid } from '@/components/members/MemberGrid'
import { FilterPanel } from '@/components/directory/FilterPanel'

export default async function DirectoryPage({
  searchParams,
}: {
  searchParams: Record<string, string>
}) {
  const filters = parseFilters(searchParams)
  const { members, count } = await searchMembers(filters)

  return (
    <div className="flex gap-8">
      <FilterPanel initialFilters={filters} />
      <MemberGrid members={members} count={count} />
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Error handling
Always use Next.js `error.tsx` boundaries at the route segment level. For server actions, return typed result objects:
```typescript
type ActionResult<T> =
  | { success: true; data: T }
  | { success: false; error: string }
```

