## Key decisions + rationale

**Why Supabase over Prisma + separate auth?**
Supabase gives RLS at the database level — the access control for a members-only platform is enforced at the data layer, not just the application layer. Magic link auth means no password management. Storage handles avatars. One service handles four concerns.

**Why App Router (not Pages Router)?**
Server components let you co-locate data fetching with the UI that needs it. The directory page fetches filtered members on the server — no loading spinner, no client-side state management for initial load. Layouts handle the auth shell cleanly.

**Why not Algolia for search?**
Postgres `tsvector` + `pg_trgm` + GIN indexes handles the search needs of a community up to ~50,000 members without a separate service. Migrate to Algolia when search latency becomes a real user complaint, not before.

**Why shadcn/ui?**
Components are copied into the project (not imported from a package), so they're fully customisable without fighting a design system. This matters as the platform develops its own visual identity.

**Deferred intentionally:**
- Real-time feed / community posts — cold-start content problem, adds moderation surface
- Direct messaging — same; also complicates GDPR/data handling
- Public profiles — the members-only wall is a core value prop
- Company/team profiles — Phase 2 or beyond
- Mobile app — PWA first if needed
